Text: What we've done this week.
Similar to last week we had 3 team meetings, one with Jeremiah and further implemented code in the UI and experimented with more algorithms in the back end.
The good
We managed to get a decent amount of work done as a team and Jeremiah seemed to be impressed with what we presented with him so far.
The UI has started to improve a lot since we started on it and will hopefully continue to improve as we go along.
As a team we did a good job of keeping in touch with each other and taking initiatives to get tasks done and are slowly finding solutions to get our project complete.
Things to improve as a team
The main aspect to improve as a team is too make sure we have a clear list of priorities for our project so we are not spending too much time on aspects that we will not implement.
We addressed this on Friday and tried to figure out what features we really need and broke down each step to know what we need to do.
I'm hoping we can continue to prioritise and execute, so that we have a productive last two weeks.
I also feel that at times we get caught speaking about tasks at a abstract level for too long and not figure out how to actually implement these solutions.
This could be addressed by testing ideas as we discuss them to figure out if we can actually do them.
Things I could do betterI felt I spent too much time on features for our app that we may not utilise given the time period.
I focused to much on things that were nice to have and not essential and was a little frustrated as I had a similar experience in the last project.
However, this might be a factor in all projects as there will always be a change of direction in the project.
To help combat this issue this week, I will need to make sure I have a full understanding of the high priority tasks that need to get done for the week.
This understanding will also need to be paired with better time management to ensure I am not spending too much time on non essential tasks.
Goals for next week.
The goals for the upcoming week are to finally get a meeting with the anatomy department, as we weren't able to secure for the last two weeks.
The technical tasks for our project are to add a merge and split function and hopefully a method to allow a user to choose custom labels for each class in the image.
General thoughts
The project has been going pretty smoothly as a team but I have again felt a sense that I have not done enough work towards the project.
If I were to look at the hours spent on the project I have most likely spent much longer than 20 hours on it, but there is a lingering feeling of not enough has been done.
I'm beginning to realise this is something that has been present throughout all three projects and may be more related to my own expectations of what we can produce.
It might be that I am too hard on myself for not being able to produce something that I cannot yet do given my skills and the project timeframes.
I feel I should most likely just focus on learning things that are of high importance to the project as opposed to trying to master everything in a few weeks.
With only two weeks remaining, I'm also left with a bittersweet feeling as things are almost coming to an end for course work this year.
It has been a great year so far with new friendships and will be sad to see some people go.
Gogo make the most of things as we head to the finish line!
Overall
